      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s really similar to split-brain described in the multi-site documentation[1].\nWhen we have push on top of the reference. This could be a new commit in a branch or the change of an existing commit. Master 1 checks if local HEAD is equal to the sha1 stored in global ref-db. If yes Master 1 apply the change and update the global ref-db. Next we have another push for that reference but this time on Master 2, Master 2 checks if local HEAD is equal sha1 stored in global ref-db. If Master 2 jgit cache is not up to date because of NFS caching it will see old sha1 so it will not match with global ref-db. Ref update will be rejected on Master 2.\n\n1. https://gerrit.googlesource.com/plugins/multi-site/+/refs/heads/master/DESIGN.md#avoid-split-brain",
